-- 
SPAIN DAYBOOK: Cabinet to Pass Decree on Capital for Lenders

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-02-18T06:53:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/spain-daybook-cabinet-to-pass-decree-on-capital-for-lenders.html
  Spain ’s Cabinet is due to pass a
decree increasing capital requirements for lenders and setting a
deadline for banks to meet the new rules.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Finance Minister Elena Salgado and Deputy Prime Minister
Alfredo Perez Rubalcaba give a news conference at 1:45 p.m. CET
after the weekly Cabinet meeting.  ECONOMY:
*The Bank of Spain reports December bad-loans ratio.
*Salgado will allow Spain’s savings banks to consider generic
provisions and preferred shares as core capital, El  Confidencial 
Reported, citing the text of the decree.  EQUITIES:
*Bolsas y Mercados Espanoles, the manager of Spain’s stock
exchange, will report fourth-quarter earnings before the market
opens in Madrid.
*Bancaja Inversiones SA said in a regulatory filing it will sell
its 5 percent stake in  Enagas  SA via an accelerated bookbuilding
coordinated by Deutsche Bank AG.
  Ferrovial SA ’s BAA Ltd., the owner of London’s Heathrow
airport, will likely have to sell two of its U.K. airports after
the Supreme Court refused to hear an appeal of a decision by a
competition regulator.
*Grupo Empresarial San Jose SA, via its Concesionaria San Jose
Tecnocontrol SA unit, obtained $250 million from a consortium of
banks to finance a hospital project in Chile, the company said
in a regulatory filing.  MARKETS:
*The  IBEX 35 Index  advanced 0.6 percent to 11,113. *The spread
between Spanish and German 10-year borrowing costs widened to
218 basis points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in  Madrid  at 
